caption:

They do not prove that nurses cheat more than any other profession overall ‚Äî they only show that among certain samples of people admitting infidelity, a significant portion work in healthcare.
The Gallup data suggest the opposite in terms of public perception of honesty and ethics for nurses.
Conclusion
So, to your question: Which survey said that nurses cheat more than other professions? ‚Äî There's no robust survey I found that supports that exact statement. The closest are adultery‚Äêsite surveys which suggest healthcare workers show up prominently in their samples, but that is not the same as proving nurses cheat more than all other professions.
If you like, I can check further academic literature to see if there has been a formal study comparing cheating rates across professions (workplace misconduct or infidelity).
